Wawne dates back to before the original{Domesday Book. { Its 12th Century church was probably already built when{Meaux Abbey}was founded a mile to the North. It was the monks of Meaux who developed{ {Le Wyk}as an outlet port for their wollen trade. This village later became{Kingston_Upon_Hull.}
To the South_East of Wawne lies{Swine. This is the site of a hoard of Roman coins and a pre_dissolution nunery.
To the West lies the{River Hull.}A ferry linked Wawne and{Thearne}which lies close to the main Beverley Road. It was still functioning 50 years ago as a raft pulled across by ropes.
